Governor Rochas Okorocha of Imo state celebrated Easter by re-enacting the death and crucifixion of Jesus Christ . The outspoken governor took the solemn task with all seriousness as he was pictured in his underwear, strapped to a makeshift cross, with an improvised crown of thorns and “blood-stains” on his white undergarment. The photo of Okorocha’s crucifixion is currently making the rounds on Twitter with users having a go with hilarious captions. 